This part of the Palatine along which we have just passed, the Romans called Ger-malm, in remembrance of the wonderful rescue of the twins, Romulus and Remus. The Tiber near by, into whose raging floods they were to have ‚been thrown, had just at that time overflowed its banks and filled the hollows be- tween the Capitoline, Palatine, and Aventine Hills.
